			<ns0:name>matthews...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/110120698207258198636/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We ran into similar issues during development of a .NET application.  This issue
exists in many localized versions of Windows XP (Italian is "Programmi" for example).
Our solution was to use the Windows dynamic links:
%programfiles%
%temp%
etc.
This should find the system's default "Program Files" path on any version of Windows.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2009-06-17T13:03:47.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2009-06-17T13:03:47.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 5 by matthews...@gmail.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2#c5" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2/comments/full/5" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>